    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Molly, this cake sounds delicious.  I love the flavor and scent of oranges in a cake.  I make one of Clotilde&#39;s all the time, but that one is loaded with butter.  </p>
<p>When I make Craig Claiborne&#39;s Linzertorte and Marcella&#39;s Carrot Cake, I use almonds that still have the skins on because their color is important to the result.  Do you use raw almonds with or without the skins in this recipe?</p>
<p>Lovely to hear from you.  I&#39;ve never had a miss with one of your recipes.  Thanks.</p>
