  <li id="comment-17960" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/00097330009175643958" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Mercedes</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=869#comment-17960"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-02-14T20:31:45-05:00">Sunday, February 14, 2010 at 8:31 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I believe most of the recipes for this sort of cake stem from Claudia Roden&#39;s Orange Almond Cake, which was published back in the 70&#39;s, and is actually a traditional Middle Eastern cake. I know the recipes from Nigella and others specifically attribute it to Claudia Roden. </p>
<p>It&#39;s common to find this cake in Turkey served with a big dollop of clotted cream (kaymak) on top.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=869#comment-17960' data-commentid="17960" data-postid="869" data-belowelement="comment-17960" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Mercedes" aria-label='Reply to Mercedes'>Reply</a>    </div>
