  <li id="comment-18033" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn">Anonymous</cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=869#comment-18033"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-02-21T08:40:21-05:00">Sunday, February 21, 2010 at 8:40 am</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve been making Claudia Roden&#39;s flour less orange cake for years. It&#39;s a cafe standard in Australia. Instead of boiling the oranges, I quarter them, take out the seeds, cut away the pith in the centre of the quarters and then microwave them in a bowl of water for about 15 minutes. I find microwaving the oranges results in a softer, less bitter peel.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='index.html?p=869#comment-18033' data-commentid="18033" data-postid="869" data-belowelement="comment-18033" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Anonymous" aria-label='Reply to Anonymous'>Reply</a>    </div>
