  <li id="comment-18046" class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/14558150140186925892" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Shuna Fish</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=869#comment-18046"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2010-02-23T23:03:01-05:00">Tuesday, February 23, 2010 at 11:03 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>cakes like this have recently entered my radar, mouth, repertoire, recipe box &#038;, consequently, dessert menus.</p>
<p>my only extra advice would be to alter the method slightly: emulsify oil in with whipping eggs + sugar. and then adding almond &#39;meal&#39; &#038; citrus puree. </p>
<p>this way there&#39;s no danger in overmixing the cake batter&#8211; an instruction primarily geared at developing gluten strands from the flour, which one mostly does not want in tender cake texture/crumb.</p>
<p>p.s. i adore the banner, and your photos get better and better.</p>
    </div>

