  <li id="comment-18122" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/14559331687189925332" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Nicole</a></cite></div>
      <a href="index.html?p=869#comment-18122"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2011-05-11T22:10:44-04:00">Wednesday, May 11, 2011 at 10:10 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Came across this recipe while looking for almond/olive oil cakes on the web, and thought I&#39;d give it a try. So glad I did!! Amazing cake. Thank you for posting. Instead of confectioner&#39;s sugar on top, I used the lemon pulp, a tiny bit of the leftover orange/lemon water (from the boiling stage) and several tablespoons of honey to make a glaze. It was fantastic, and helped add moisture to the slightly toasted outer layer (I used a decorative bundt-style pan instead of spring form and left it in the oven about 5 min too long). I&#39;ll be making this again! Thanks!</p>
    </div>

